HEADWORD: Devow
<hw>De*vow"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧vouer</ets>, L. <ets>devovere</ets>. See <er>Devote</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give up; to devote.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. OF. <ets>desvoer</ets>. Cf.
<er>Disavow</er>.]</ety> <def>To disavow; to disclaim.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>G. Fletcher.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Devulgarize</ent>⟦br⟧
